		<a name="62653"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/24/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 04:57:06</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=638"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=638')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=62653&amp;TOPIC_ID=7488&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=The+Growing+Role+Of+Priest+Classes&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Rich Waters said:</P><P>"Clerics are going to receive additional changes so that they have some abilities that makes them more sought after for grouping."</P><P>As a necromancer I'm stunned at this statement. It completely baffles me that probably the most important, desired, needed, required, essential class in EverQuest *needs* more help in getting a group???</P><P>Why have we not seen a similar statement from Mr. Waters or a SOE rep concerning necromancers plight about not being needed or wanted in groups? For 2 years we had to put up with Gordon Wrinn's anti-necro agenda and not once has a SOE rep ever came here and said we needed help getting in groups or even acknowledged it in such broad and expansive terms as Mr. Waters has done for clerics.</P><P>My analysis is this: Clerics are such a huge constituency in EverQuest that *their* needs take precedence over a non-essential class like a necromancer, mage or beastlord. Verant has even admitted they tune every encounter taking into account complete heal and the powers of clerics. How many encounters are tuned with necros in mind? NONE! Clerirs are such a large demographic due to high popularity of this class that SOE can't afford not to coddle them. Go check the roster on any major uber guild and see how many clerics they have vs. necromancers.</P><P>Clerics have no business complaining about the fact that they have to sit and heal. That is their role from the earliest pen and paper D&D game to EverQuest. As someone mentioned, every cleric who started one *knew* their role. Unlike necromancers who were sold a false bill of goods--we started off as damage dealers and ended up as mana feeders.</P><P>What has really changed for necromancers? The pet changes were a long time coming and they affected every pet class. I can think of only 1 change and that is the upgrade on the Emissary of Thule pet damage (if the mage community had it's way our spectre would be nerfed back into oblivion). All other changes to our class have been generic changes to pets in general. Just for once I would like to see Rich Waters and the team at EQ sit down and talk about the necromancer class and our role in EverQuest end game encounters.</P><P>As a community we've been submitting and posting great ideas on how to improve our class to SOE for the past 3 years. Let's be honest Lawrence Poe's spell design in Luclin and Velious have been pretty lame for necromancers. Group DMF is still almost impossible to find. Gangrenous Touch of Zum`ul also very very rare. Conglaciation of Bone and it's fire version again rare drops from Vindi. Funeral Pyre is NEVER for sale on my server and if it was I and others could not afford it. SOE seems to go out of it's way to create new spells for druids, shaman and now clerics but not the necromancer.</P><P>A few months ago the cleric class got a huge boost. They got various rez spells that give various rates of experience back. This was a fundamental change to the class. As necromancers we asked SOE to find ways to help reform the essence emerald and necromancer rez ability and nothing has been done.</P><P>Dot stacking will not "fix" our class. All it will do is allow a few more necros to join a raid and fill up a few more NPC buff/debuf "slots" and now we hear that Ignite Blood may not stack with Pyro or Pyro with Funeral Pyre. Wonderful. Dot stacking should have been in the EQ engine from day 1. This just goes to show you how little SOE has even thought about the role of necromancers in EverQuest. We have been so marginalized and unimportant that only now 4 expansions later has someone even bothered to take a few hours to honestly look at this problem. That speaks volumes of where necromancers fit into the "big picture" at SOE. DOT stacking is a smoke screen. It does not address the difficiencies in our class as far as being wanted in groups.</P><P>Comparing the importance of the cleric epic to the necro epic says it all about the way we've been treated as a class. I've seen guilds camp Ragefire for days just so they will have another cleric with a "rez stick". That one item is easily the most powerful unbalanced thing in EverQuest. It has torn apart servers, torn apart guilds and friendships. How many guild members consider the necromancer epic essential to their guild??? ZERO.</P><P>SOE has me baffled and shocked. What's next? Warriors, rogues and monks getting even more power? Clearly, SOE has moved on to the healer type classes now and that worries me because I believe we are still not fixed as a class. We have been beaten down for so long that we rejoiced at a few extra points of damage for the spectre pet. Other than generic pet changes, that is all we have really seen from Verant. To make matters worse we got a crummy Luclin skeleton graphic and lost our red pets and Lichform. So here SOE goes again and is giving clerics better pets?!?</P><P>The real problem that need to be addressed is the limitation of the 6 person group. That artificial cap is the fundamental problem in EverQuest today because if your class is non-essential than you will have less of a chance to get invited into a group. After you fill a group with a warrior, cleric, shaman, enchanter, rogue/monk/wizard that is when you consider a marginalized class like the necromancer. If EverQuest is to survive for much longer the 6 person group cap will have to be eliminated. It is the true source of most class balancing problems today.</P><P>Our fight to be needed and wanted on guild raids is not over. It's time for someone at SOE to display some real creativity and imagination and find a way to make necromancers a necessary part of the EverQuest endgame. Every raid should *need* necros, just as every raid *needs* clerics, warriors, rogues, monks, shaman, wizards, etc. Giving clerics more utility in groups is like giving Bill Gates welfare. It's just plain wrong.</P><P>Dornette<BR>60 necromancer<BR>The Nameless</P><P><BR>Edited by - Dornette on 08/24/2002  05:18:41<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
