		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=9184"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=9184')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=62666&amp;TOPIC_ID=7488&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=The+Growing+Role+Of+Priest+Classes&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I mean no disrespect but, never judge a man/class until you have walked a mile in his shoes. I've been playing my cleric for 3 years now and until these changes, my role has been as healer and ALL my best spells worth using were designed around being the best at that role. I, quite frankly had no problems with this at all. Every expanstion has given clerics one thing, some better way to heal, be it through larger buffs to take advantage of CH and make it more efficient or HoT's which have a nice heal/mana ratio and are wonderful for controlling aggro. What was given up for this? A total lack of any utility or damage output and the fact that clerics are on the same damage table as INT casters for melee. I was content with this and truly enjoyed my role and would have been happy if this role had continued. It did not. With the release of Luclin and the Advent of AA abilites, better weapons and armor for melees, etc. tanks became tougher and quite frankly were quite capable of soloing. Now if just about ANY tank can solo, what REAL need is there for a cleric? Barring CT and Sraa, just about any group can get along fine without a cleric and still make good exp. That is the crux of the issue for clerics, we were designed for grouping and were fine with it until our role of healing was slowly replaced by damage output and mitigation. </P><P>     With the addition of these new heals for our fellow priests we bring less to the table of a group; no ports, sow, slow, haste, stat buffs, nukes, dots, etc. (heck, clerics do not even have a simple invisibilty spell and I am sure you know how useful IU is) and our viability in a group is even lessened more in what was once our own primary role. Well, if I cannot find a group, solo is the answer, right? Well, yea and no. I am one of the fortunate clerics through a combination of good gear and a nice chunk of AA, who can actually solo with some degree of efficiency and margin of saftey. I root 'n rot with my rather ineffcient undead dots (THANK VI for the Hammer of the Sun, a clickie 750 point undead dot is just what the doctor ordered). This simply is not the case for the majority of clerics. </P><P>While on the raid scene clerics were just fine (and I am more than happy to share some of the healing burden with my fellow priests :) ), in a group setting for a class that pretty much HAD to group for any reasonable exp gain, being pigeon holed into a specialization that is becoming less and less necessary was becoming problematic at best. Frankly, I would rather group and heal, I ENJOY the role but, times they are a changing and this role is not NEARLY as viable as it used to be. Clerics needed something every other class had and that is an OPTION. Seems we will be getting it and I am glad of it. </P><P>I hope this has made some sense to you and a little understanding of what it is like in another man's shoes.</P><P>Venerable Lith Ahntalon<BR>60 High Priest in the service of Tunare</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
