        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I would like to share my view of this, as a cleric. </P><P>Someone said it already, far more eloquently than I can... with gear nowdays, who needs clerics?  I am on Xegony, and I OFTEN go for hours LFG.  While in front of me, a rogue or monk or paladin or SK solos blissfully.  Eventually, they get an add, and THEN, they come begging me to bail them out... and now their add is on me, and I'm desperately trying to root it off of me as it picks me up and throws me around like a rag doll.  While the "soloing" yak screams at me for KSing him.  I'm in a life or death struggle here, all I want is this thing OFF OF ME, and he's afraid I'm KSING??  Is the guy insane?</P><P>If I tried to kill that, I would end up OOM, 1 bub of health, and the mob at half.  IF I just so HAPPEN to have offensive spells up to begin with.  My ONLY offensive spells break root, so everytime I nuke, I must root again, and heal myself again.  That's a LOT of mana, and do you think I specialized in Evoc, LOL!</P><P>I'm level 54, and I'm pretty much out in the cold.  I bring nothing to groups that have a shaman or druid in them.  My rez isn't good enough, my heals are FAR MORE than adequate, and I bring little else to the table.  Oo, my nukes.  Ha, I caught you snickering!  See?  Wait, I know, my ubermelee!  Yeah, that time you outright laughed, I saw it.  Or MOK!  My 15 point DS is far superior to a druid DS!  And you KNOW you need that DS if you have a slower in the group...  Hey, there's my pet!  Yes, my lovely, overpowered pet that you KNOW you just MUST have!</P><P>See, what everyone appears to be missing here is that when on an exp grind, you don't need the best healer.  You need a GOOD ENOUGH healer, and this spell will make both shamans and druids GOOD ENOUGH.  As well as them bringing MORE to the table than a cleric can possibly imagine bringing.</P><P>Now, in a way, I'm happy!  If groups can't find a cleric, they can STILL go play.  That's wonderful!  But what does that do to my level 54 cleric?  It makes her dead weight to exp groups in anywhere but the very most extreme places.  I love chardok, but I'm already replacable there.  I know for a FACT that a level 52 to 56 group can easily hold the Observer and the bridge with just a druid who has Superior Heal.  Or a shaman who does, and it's even easier with the shaman than the druid.  And, the rate of pull does NOT change if you take someone out and put in a cleric.  You must remove someone who does damage to add a cleric... so the pull rate remains constant.  It jumps for the first few minutes, because the shaman or druid who left leaves buffs behind.</P><P>Now, as for what clerics do besides healing, here's my typical "way of doing things".  My job, as I see it is to throw a MOR on the mob, DS stacks with others, thank goodness, then MOK if it has a DS (have POG bp, it's a right clicky effect).  I stun and root mobs off of the enchanter, I refresh buffs.  I nuke if, and only IF I have "extra" mana- that's above 60%.  Then, I sit down.  Now, when I'm lucky, the mob is gone by then and I can MOK, MOR, and stun some more, drop a heal on the warrior/sk/ranger/pally.</P><P>Now, here's the really hard part about being a cleric in a group.  You MUST stay alert.  If you lose that edge, someone dies.  So, how does someone who must sit and med, sit and med, sit and med stay alert?  Either we make a way, or we just simply fall down on the job.  I see SO many clerics who just simply fall down.  You never KNOW when the peaceful routine will be shattered by the enchanter getting a freak train of resists, or a train coming through, or someone goes LD...  and you can NOT turn your eyes away from those life bars.  My WORLD, my whole mindset is THOSE HP BARS.  That's my FOCUS, above and beyond all else.  I don't CARE how fast the mob dies, I care about my group's HPs to the exclusion of chat, mobs, etc.  </P><P>When I help with crowd control, it's because of THOSE HP BARS (tm).  When I do anything I do, it's THOSE HP BARS that are the driving force behind it.  And when someone dies, I suffer a very REAL guilt.  I fuss over each death, worrying it in my mind, 'how did I fail, what should I have done, where'd I go wrong'.  I get unbelievable rudeness from people, they all think they can do my job, that it's SO simple.  But they fail to realize.. often, I am making life/death choices for others.  This is HARD.  Should I heal the enchanter, or the tank?  Without either one, I'm dead.. so what do I do?  Do YOU want that responsibility?</P><P>And being needed on raids.  yes, we ARE needed on raids.  God, I'm so SICK of how needed I am on raids.  Please, please, can't I JUST GROUP today??  MUST I go to X, Y, or Z's epic raid tonight??  *sigh*  Yes, I must, because who else is there?  Yet, when it's time to group, do you HONESTLY think that X, Y, or Z invites me to group?  No, because they don't NEED me then.  They beg me to raid, but don't need me to group.  And that's ALREADY!  The druid and shaman heals aren't even live!  I wonder if you know how it feels to have people BEGGING you to stay up until 5, 6, and 7 am your time so they can continue raiding?  I am GLAD they're making it so druids and shamans can take my spot IF THEY MUST.  Oh so glad of that!!  I'm so tired of the guilt of leaving raids.  "Cleric's leaving, raid's over."  </P><P>And yet, people wonder why there are so few clerics... it's SO hard to level up, yet we get these endless guilt trips, the constant pressures to raid.  The vast majority of clerics are 'bots.  Why?  Because it's "so easy" to be a cleric, right?  Because people obviously WANT to be clerics, that's why there are so many... </P><P>And before you ask why I remain playing my cleric, I'm not.  My alt is level 47 now.  I can't handle the pressure.  I can't handle being LFG for HOURS, and yes, contrary to what you think, I DO go looking for a group for HOURS.  See, people either have their own cleric 'bot they're leveling in group/partnership, or they already have a cleric 'bot they can log on to get the all important GOOD REZ.  Or, they can just go ask that clicker cleric two camps over for a rez, and guilt trip them about how they should do it for free since it's a clicky...</P><P><BR>(EDIT:  And by the way, when *I* am LFG for HOURS, I can't "just go solo" to make SOME exp.  I must simply LFG until someone takes pity on me, or there are no druids available *cough*.)</P><P>Edited by - Kelial on 08/29/2002  12:29:41<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
