        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=64341&amp;TOPIC_ID=7488&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=The+Growing+Role+Of+Priest+Classes&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Wow, Kelial; that was quite a post.  I had never thought about the role/life of a cleric that way.  I hope that the proposed changes VI is thinking about actually help your class out.  It sounds like your raid responsibilities will be get easier, but you will suffer in general XP groups.</P><P>It seems like there are not as many clerics at my level (mid-30s) as there should be.  In the zones I fight it, there might be one or two clerics at the most out of 30-50 people.  Amazingly, I have been the main healer (/boggle) in most of my groups.  You know how long it takes a necro to heal a tank-type up from two bubbles of health?? LOL</P><P>Grouping is a problem though.  I wish something could/would be done to increase the grouping ability of some classes.  I like grouping because I like to talk (I can hear you saying..."Noooo?").  The other night I shout for a group and some moron shouts back, "You dont need a group, you can solo."  Wow, what insight!  I have played a necro for 34 levels and NEVER knew that we could solo!!!  I am so glad he pointed that out to me.  The only reason I bring that up is that it reflects a broad attitude many players have for necros: you can solo so we don't want you in our groups.  Makes me mad sometimes.</P><P>Anyway, I hope VI manages the final changes well.  I don't want to see the clerics turn into a bot class and I sure don't want to see everyone playing druids and shamans.  Balance and fun is all I want.</P><P>Vinsome Darkwalker</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
